How to run python terminal in sublime:
Sublime ->Tools -> Build System -> New Build System

Copy and paste the following in the file:

{
    "cmd": ["cmd", "/c", "start", "cmd", "/k", "python", "$file"]
}

Save it as “PythonTerminal”

It should be saved as “PythonTerminal.sublime-build”

Now select PythonTerminal in 

Sublime -> Tools -> Build System ->PythonTerminal

If you don’t do this, the input will have bugs and errors in sublime. 
